    },
    "se2": {
      "text": "<typewriter>We will now need a suitable weapon.\nWeapons that have <rainb>\"Casts spells from equipped Spell Book\"</rainb> will be able to use the spell book while some may not be able to and already has spells on it.",
      "illustrations": [
        "lookup",
		"seweapon"
      ],
	  "choices": [
        {
          "next": "manurunes",
          "text": "Mana / Runes"
        },
        {
          "next": "spellengine",
          "text": "Back (Spell Book)"
        },
        {
          "next": "end",
          "text": "End "
        }
      ]
    },
    "manurunes": {
      "text": "<typewriter>Runes (Spell Engine Mods, not for Archon) are craftable and you can carry an almost infinite amount of them while mana are finite and will run out after a certain amount \nMana (Spell Engine Mods & Archon) can be increased through armor or accessories. The more mana you use, the more damage you deal overtime.",
      "illustrations": [
        "lookup",
		"manarunes"
      ],
	  "choices": [
        {
          "next": "introduction",
          "text": "Back"
        },
        {
          "next": "end",
          "text": "end"
        }
      ]
    },
    "ar2": {
      "text": "Weapons that has this <rainb>\"Spell: None\"</rainb> will be able to use Archon's Spells you've learnt. Shift Right-clicking will shift through the spells you've learnt.",
      "illustrations": [
        "lookup",
		"archonspell"
      ],
